12/05/2010
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Four people were killed early Wednesday (May 12th) in a shoot-out between Macedonian police and apparent smugglers in the village of Radusa, near the Kosovo border. The interior ministry says no policemen were injured. According to preliminary reports, police attempted to stop a vehicle that appeared to be smuggling weapons across the border. Those inside the vehicle reportedly started shooting at police. (Makfax, A1, Alsat-M, AP, AFP - 12/05/10)
